
MODULE
Getopt::Long

EXAMPLE CODE
my ($domain, $node);
GetOptions('domain=s' => \$domain
	   'node=i'   => \$node); 

Command Line:
script.pl --domain Archaea --node 5

DESCRIPTION
'Archaea' will be assigned to $domain
'5'       will be assigned to $node 

The '=s' indicates that your argument is a string. 
If its not added, variable will hold 1 or 0.
The '=i' indicates that your argument is an integer